         <abstract>
            <p>In this note, we give the exact distribution of a scaled condition number used by Demmel to model the probability that matrix inversion is difficult. Specifically, consider a random matrix A and the scaled condition number κ&lt;sub&gt;D&lt;/sub&gt;(A) = |A|&lt;sub&gt;F&lt;/sub&gt; · |A&lt;sup&gt;-1&lt;/sup&gt;|. Demmel provided bounds for the condition number distribution when A has real or complex normally distributed elements. Here, we give the exact formula.</p>
          </abstract>
